{"id":6606,"category_id":6,"creator":"محرك","owner":"BBC","created_at":"28/01/2011","title":"هل يتحمل العالم انفجاراً سكانيا؟","pictures":"//wscdn.bbc.co.uk/worldservice/assets/images/2011/01/13/110113154023_pop226.jpg","active":1,"views":427,"content":"Hello and welcome to BBC Xtra English!\r\nExperts are saying that the defining challenge of this century will be a huge increase in the world’s population.\r\nThey are saying that by the year 2075, a population explosion will lead to nine and a half billion people living on the planet.\r\nA new report about population growth by the Institute of Mechanical Engineers looking at how technology can help with large increases in the world’s population has just been published.\r\nOne of the practical ideas that the mechanical engineers have suggested is to reduce food waste by storing it efficiently.\r\nThey believe that whilst we can produce enough food for a larger number of people, we lose a lot of that food by not storing it properly.\r\nDr Tom Fox from the Institute of Mechanical Engineers told the BBC that in developing countries something like fifty percent of food is wasted between being harvested in the field and taken to market place because of poor storage and lack of refrigeration.\r\nOn the other hand, Dr Fox said that in countries like the UK and the US, too much food is wasted by people buying food in supermarkets that they don’t end up eating.\r\nThere are other technological improvements which could be made to protect resources – one way to save water can be to capture rain water and use it to replenish the underground water stocks\r\nInterestingly, the report does not call for a limit to the number of children people should be allowed to have.\r\nThis suggests that the authors do believe the earth’s resources are capable of sustaining a huge population increase.\r\nDoes a population explosion worry you? Why? Write to us in English!\r\nهل تخاف من حدوث انفجار سكاني؟ لماذا؟ اكتب لنا بالإنجليزية \r\nprog\r\nprog\r\n.لاستخدام هذا الملف لابد من تشغيل برنامج النصوص \"جافا\"، وأحدث الإصدارات من برنامج \"فلاش بلاير\"\r\nأحدث إصدارات برنامج \"فلاش بلاير\" متاحة هنايمكن التشغيل باستخدام برنامج \"ريال بلاير\"، أو \"ويندوز ميديا بلاير\"\r\nPopulation explosion\r\nانفجار سكاني\r\nInstitute of Mechanical Engineers \r\nمعهد المهندسين الميكانيكيين\r\nPractical \r\nعملي\r\nReduce\r\nتخفيض\r\nFood waste\r\nإهدار الطعام\r\nStoring\r\nتخزين\r\nRefrigeration\r\nتبريد\r\nTechnological improvements\r\nتطورات تكنولوجية\r\nResources\r\nموارد\r\nSustaining \r\nتحمل/تعول/تكفل \r\nwords\r\nwords\r\n.لاستخدام هذا الملف لابد من تشغيل برنامج النصوص \"جافا\"، وأحدث الإصدارات من برنامج \"فلاش بلاير\"\r\nأحدث إصدارات برنامج \"فلاش بلاير\" متاحة هنايمكن التشغيل باستخدام برنامج \"ريال بلاير\"، أو \"ويندوز ميديا بلاير\"\r\nYour comments\r\n*Required Fields\r\nYour Feedback:Your Contact Details:\r\nName:\r\n  \r\nEmail *\r\n  \r\nTown, Country\r\n  \r\nTelephone\r\n   Your Message:\r\nComment * \r\n (500 maximum characters)  Disclaimer: \r\nI do not mind being contacted back by the BBC in relation to this comment.","presentationStyle":1}